original: Lenhoff, Erik Gustav Einar, kyrkoherde, Braås, f. 28/12/05 i Lenhovda, Krono’b. 1., av folksk :lär. Karl Gustav Karlsson o. Ester Nilsson. G. 36 ni. Esther Gustavsson. Barn: Sven f. 37, Margareta 39, Karin 42, Helena 45. — Studrex. i Lund 25, teol. fil. ex. där 28, teol. kand., prakt. teol. prov samt prästv. 32. Tjg. som pastradj. o. v. pastor i Odensjö, v. kommin. i Älm-hult samt kommin. i Drev o. Horna-ryds förs. pastorat 45, tilltr. 46.
translated: Lenhoff, Erik Gustav Einar, parish pastor, Braås, born on December 28, 1905 in Lenhovda, Kronoberg's County 1st district, son of elementary school teacher Karl Gustav Karlsson and Ester Nilsson. Married in 1936 to Esther Gustavsson. Children: Sven, born in 1937, Margareta, born in 1939, Karin, born in 1942, Helena, born in 1945. Completed studies in Lund in 1925, received a bachelor's degree in theology in 1928, theological candidate, practical theological examination, and ordained as a priest in 1932. Worked as a curate and assistant pastor in Odensjö, assistant curate in Älmhult, and curate in Drev and Hornaryd parish from 1945, assumed duties in 1946.
